                  <persName id="t18300415-337-person2799">
                  EDWARD 
                  CHEAPER
               <interp inst="t18300415-337-person2799" type="surname" value="CHEAPER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-337-person2799" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-337-person2799" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18300415-337-viclabel1822" type="occupation">boot-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-337-victim2798 t18300415-337-viclabel1822"></join>. On the 24th of December the prisoner, whom I had seen once before, came and selected four pairs of boots, and two pairs of shoes; he directed me to send my lad with him to Langbourn-court, Fenchurch-street - I gave him an invoice of the goods; and gave my lad goods, and a receipt for the money, to deliver to the prisoner - he fully understood it was forready money, and said if I wrote a receipt, there would be a gentleman there who would pay the lad; they went away together - the lad returned with out money or boots - I apprehended the prisoner this day fortnight.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-337-person2800">
                  EDWARD 
                  GIBBS
               <interp inst="t18300415-337-person2800" type="surname" value="GIBBS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-337-person2800" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-337-person2800" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the prosecutor's errand-boy. I was to go to Langbourn-court with the prisoner; master gave me a receipt to give the gentleman for the money - the prisoner heard that; I was not to part with<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183004150143"></xptr>them without the money - the prisoner took me down <placeName id="t18300415-337-crimeloc1823">Jewry-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-337-crimeloc1823" type="placeName" value="Jewry-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-337-crimeloc1823" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-337-off1820 t18300415-337-crimeloc1823"></join>, and gave me a shilling to get changed, as he wanted some halfpence, and said he would hold the bag the while; I went into a public-house - they could not give me change, and when I came out the prisoner was gone with the goods.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. The prosecutor has known me a long time; I have been frequently at his shop.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18300415-337-verdict1824" type="verdictDescription">
